                  <span class="c00">That word would be <i>Nahrungsmittelunverträglichkeit</i> again. I just tested it and LaTeX (with `\usepackage[ngerman]{babel}`) does the same mistake as pyphen in the article (it hyphenates the word as <i>Nah-rung-smit-telun-ver-träg-lichkeit</i>).<p>To be fair, in day-to-day use problems like these will be corner cases as to my knowledge LaTeX tries to avoid hyphenation and even if it has to split a word, it has a good chance of getting it right. Also, to me this project&#x27;s focus was more on learning about neural networks than creating a better hyphenator.<span>
